{"lemma":"ه","slug":"ه","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"abbrev","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ه","root":"","pos":"P","occurrence_count":484},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adv","character","particle","pron","symbol"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n40797","n44220"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"character","gloss":"The twenty-sixth letter of the Arabic alphabet, written in the Arabic script; preceded by ن (n) and followed by و (w).","tags":["letter"]},{"pos":"symbol","gloss":"The abjad numeral representing the number five (5)"},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"him, his, it, its (bound object pronoun, referring to inanimate nouns of masculine gender)"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"AH"},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"Banū Ṭayyiʔ form of أَ (ʔa, interrogative particle)","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the Nabataean letter 𐢇 (l, “he”), derived from the Phoenician letter 𐤄 (l, “he”), from the Egyptian hieroglyph 𓀠. See also Classical Syriac ܗ (l, “he”), Hebrew ה (l, “he”), Ancient Greek Ε (E), Latin E.\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *ha. Cognate to Hebrew הֲ־ (hă-)."},"ipa":["/haːʔ/","/h/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n40797","headword_ar":"ه","root":"h","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The twenty-sixth letter of the alphabet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA='N","text_ar":"هَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is one of the class termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haloqiy~apN","text_ar":"حَلْقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guttural"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and is a radical letter, except when written with two dots,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for which, and for the pronominal values of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., see the Supplement. ―         -b2-  As a numeral it denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"five."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n44220","headword_ar":"ه","root":"h","body":[{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu","text_ar":"هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the vowel of this pron. is sometimes, in a case of pause, transferred to the preceding letter: and this is always done in modern Arabic. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ho","text_ar":"هْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"subjoined in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hun~aho","text_ar":"هُنَّهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the like: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDu","text_ar":"اَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haA","text_ar":"هَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanobiyhN","text_ar":"تَنْبِيهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is said by some to be used as an inceptive, without any meaning but inception. (See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*A","text_ar":"ذا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalimapu tanobiyhK","text_ar":"كَلِمَةُ تَنْبِيهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nbh","text_ar":"نبه"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA","text_ar":"تَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". When followed by a pronoun, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hw","text_ar":"هو"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., it is best rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lo."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"of pausation: see remarks on a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiynN","text_ar":"حِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA","text_ar":"بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTaA^a bihaA","text_ar":"حَطَاَ بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and many phrases syn. therewith, is app. for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@sotihi","text_ar":"بِا@سْتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTaA^a","text_ar":"حَطَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}